

A simple paint application built using Python and Tkinter. This application allows users to draw on a canvas with various brush colors and sizes, making it a fun and interactive tool for creating digital art.

## Features

- Choose brush color from a color palette
- Adjust brush size using a slider
- Real-time drawing while dragging the mouse
- Clear the canvas with a single click
- User-friendly and responsive interface

## Getting Started

To run the Paint App on your local machine, follow these steps:

1. Ensure you have Python installed. You can download it from the official website: [Python Downloads](https://www.python.org/downloads/)

2. Clone this repository to your local machine using Git or download the ZIP file.

3. Open a terminal (command prompt) and navigate to the project directory.

4. Install the required dependencies (Tkinter is usually included with Python):

   ```bash
   # Install periodictable library (required for the periodic table viewer feature)
   pip install periodictable
   ```

5. Run the Paint App:

   ```bash
   python paint_app.py
   ```

6. The Paint App window should open, and you can start drawing on the canvas right away!

## How to Use

- Select the brush color by clicking the "Brush Color" button and choosing a color from the color palette.
- Adjust the brush size using the "Brush Size" slider. Slide it left or right to increase or decrease the size of the brush.
- Click and drag the left mouse button on the canvas to draw with the selected color and brush size.
- To clear the canvas and start over, click the "Clear Canvas" button.

